The paper deals with constructing coresets for range counting queries on uncertain data, which involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The use of probability densities and thresholds in the queries suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The construction of coresets involves geometric considerations, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the use of discrepancy-based approaches suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT).
